// The `privshape` device's datasheet states a `Hidden[4]` storage requirement, but `Hidden` is defined
// only in the impl's `#module` (private) band. A driver can only size a PUBLIC shape, so the
// requirement names no public shape and must error (pointing the user to make the shape public).
// RUN: %arche build -o %t %s > %t.out 2>&1 ; grep -qiE "no public shape" %t.out
#import { privshape }

main :: proc() {
  run privshape.tick;
}
